= (x - y) * (q(x^3) - 19) + y * (q(x^3) - q(y^3))
For x = y, the first term vanishes. This is the diagonal component.
For x^3 = y^3 but x != y, the second term (q(x^3) - q(y^3)) vanishes. This gives the additional constraint (x - y) * (q(x^3) - 19) = 0. Since x != y, we have q(x^3) = 19.
