OK, so the set X = {(x, y) : p(x) = p(y)} consists of the solutions to the polynomial equation p(x) - p(y) = 0. This can be factorized. Each irreducible factor gives rise to an irreducible component of X.
For the polynomial I chose:
p(x) = x * ((x^2 - 1)^9 + 1) - 19x
I can factorize p(x) - p(y) as:
p(x) - p(y) = x * ((x^2 - 1)^9 + 1) - 19x - (y * ((y^2 - 1)^9 + 1) - 19y)
= x * ((x^2 - 1)^9 + 1) - y * ((y^2 - 1)^9 + 1) - 19(x - y)
= (x - y) * ((x^2 - 1)^9 + 1) + y * ((x^2 - 1)^9 + 1 - (y^2 - 1)^9 - 1) - 19(x - y)
= (x - y) * ((x^2 - 1)^9 + 1 - 19) + y * ((x^2 - 1)^9 - (y^2 - 1)^9)
For x = y, the first term vanishes. This gives the diagonal component.
For x = -y, the term (x^2 - 1)^9 - (y^2 - 1)^9 = 0 because x^2 = y^2. This gives another component with the condition (x^2 - 1)^9 + 1 - 19 = 0 or (x^2 - 1)^9 = 18.
